    "instructions": [
        "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C). Line a large sheet pan with parchment paper.",
        "Spread asparagus, cherry tomatoes, and red onion on the pan. Drizzle with 2 tablespoons olive oil, sprinkle with Italian herbs, salt, and pepper. Toss to coat.",
        "Push vegetables to the sides of the pan and place salmon fillets in the center.",
        "Mix remaining olive oil with minced garlic and lemon juice. Brush generously over salmon fillets. Season with salt and pepper.",
        "Roast for 20-25 minutes until salmon flakes easily with a fork and vegetables are tender and slightly caramelized.",
        "Serve immediately with fresh lemon wedges."
